    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Vote for the Pool For Children's Sake</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Laura Jensen leter on May 14 article urges residents to support Somers (NY) town pool referendum (S)o</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Let's place the needs of our children first and vote yes on June 20 for a Somers town pool. For only 15 cents a day for the average taxpayer -- or an average of about $55 a year -- this is a real possibility.</p>
        <p>When we look at the big picture of who would benefit the most, it is obvious that all children will. A wonderful opportunity lies before us to provide a much needed safe, social and recreational outlet for children of all ages.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Let's place the needs of our children first and vote yes on June 20 for a Somers town pool. For only 15 cents a day for the average taxpayer -- or an average of about $55 a year -- this is a real possibility.</p>
        <p>When we look at the big picture of who would benefit the most, it is obvious that all children will. A wonderful opportunity lies before us to provide a much needed safe, social and recreational outlet for children of all ages.</p>
        <p>A town pool will not only make Somers a more desirable place to live but will also create a greater sense of community. With all the planned buffers surrounding the pool, Somers' rural character will not be compromised.</p>
        <p>LAURA JENSEN  Somers</p>
      </block>
